Karpov Draws Anand in Game Three of FIDE Chess Final 
FIDE world chess champion Anatoly Karpov of Russia drew with Indian
challenger Viswanathan Anand in game three of their six-game series in
Lausanne, Switzerland, on Sunday.
The two players agreed to reach an early draw after the 19th move, and
the contest so far see each of them has a win and a draw.
Anand, who beat Karpov in game two, will take advantages by starting
white in two of the remaining games.
Karpov, 46, is regarded as one of the greatest players in the chess
history.
